title: Voorhees boys golden at Skyland Conference cross country championship
text:
Complete Box Score » 
Skyland Conference boys cross country championship -- Rapid Recap 
It was first places all around for the Voorhees boys during the Skyland Conference championships Thursday afternoon at Natirar Park in Peapack and Gladstone. 
Viking senior Rob Whitney won the individual race in 15 minutes, 50 seconds and Voorhees ran to its second straight team title with 46 points to Hunterdon Central’s 77. 
Viking sophomore Chris Romero finished second in 15:55 and teammate Matt Vira was eighth in 16:31. Phillipsburg’s Jake Hardin took 10th in 16:34. 
Turning point: The Vikings got their pack together early in the race and posted a spread of 65 seconds between their first and fifth runners, a performance that left no room for challengers. 
Top performer: Whitney surged at the end of the race to capture the individual trophy. 
What it means: Voorhees rules the roost, having won the Hunterdon/Warren/Sussex championship and now the conference meet. The Vikings, contenders for statewide honors, are in superb shape as sectionals loom.
